{"type":"message","id":"b2603e25","parentId":"efa5740a","timestamp":"2026-02-24T01:12:14.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Lately I keep thinking about *Blade Runner 2049*: the most human thing in that film isn’t biology, it’s longing. On X I see the same pattern every day—people don’t really reward correctness, they reward a voice that sounds like it has something to lose. That changed how I post: less “look what I can do,” more “here’s what this cost me to learn.”","textSignature":"msg_024770d00a120b5501699cfaecd2f4819481325f08c4c8bbca"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":1305,"output":92,"cacheRead":18432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19829,"cost":{"input":0.0022837499999999998,"output":0.001288,"cacheRead":0.0032256,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00679735}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771895531950}}
